main event: A civilian pilot observed a fusiform, arm-shaped object heading north at an estimated speed of 10,000 - 24,000 mph near Rehoboth Beach, Delaware, on June 2, 1947.
interesting points: The observer has 9 years of flying experience,This was the second sighting of such an object for the observer,The object was reported to be heading north,The speed of the object is significantly high,Positive identification of the object could not be made due to insufficient details provided.
witness description: civilian pilot with 9 years of experience
